    "section_help_text_WXwPgW": {
      "type": "section-help-text",
      "name": "section-help-text",
      "settings": {
        "title": "The complete, no-nonsense guide for parents",
        "description": "<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">If you're buying gloves for your child, chances are this is new territory. Maybe it’s their first season in goal. Maybe they’re all in — and suddenly obsessed with keeping clean sheets.</p>\n<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">Whatever stage they’re at, here's what you need to know:<br>Gloves aren't just accessories — they're essential equipment.<br>And buying the right pair will make a huge difference in their confidence, safety, and performance.</p>\n<p class=\"section-help-text__text\">This is the guide we wish every parent had before buying their first pair.</p>"
      }
    },
    "section_help_content_fafB6k": {
      "type": "section-help-content",
      "blocks": {
        "row_RURRAx": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "What type of glove does your child actually need?",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">Here’s what most parents don’t get told:</p>\n<ul class=\"section-content__list\">\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">You don’t need the most expensive glove.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">You don’t need adult gloves in a smaller size</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">And you definitely don’t need cheap Amazon specials with no grip and weak stitching</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">You need gloves designed for junior keepers who are still learning how to dive, catch, recover, and fall — because that’s where most damage happens.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">That’s what we build ours for.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/d2870f4df3ceb003e34eff919533663a3e7ed498.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_eL3Vmg": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Why junior keepers wear through gloves quickly (and why it's not a fault)",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">If you’re wondering why your child’s gloves seem to wear down fast — you’re not alone.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">We hear this all the time.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">\n\"They’ve only had them 3 weeks!\"<br>\"The palm is peeling already.\"<br>\"Is this a defect?\"\n</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">It’s not. It’s exactly what’s meant to happen.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Youth goalkeepers are still learning technique — which means they often land palms-first, drag gloves on turf, or push off using the latex instead of their fists.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">It’s part of the process. It’s how they figure things out.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">That’s why we use Giga latex on all our junior gloves.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">It gives them solid grip, but holds up far better than the soft pro-grade latex we use on adult models.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Our gloves aren’t built to stay perfect.<br>They’re built to take the hits, session after session.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/c5b05844ccf117320861b30696b32d16586022b1.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_ndw6BP": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Why glove fit matters more than you think",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">A glove that’s too big means your child can’t feel the ball — they’ll struggle to catch, and they’ll feel like the glove is getting in the way.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Too small, and they’ll be uncomfortable or split at the seams during play.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Here’s how to get it right:</p>\n<ul class=\"section-content__list\">\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Measure from the base of their palm to the tip of their middle finger</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Add 1cm</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Match to the correct size in our glove size chart →</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Pro tip: Don't size up “to grow into them.” You’ll just make everything harder.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/Group_39697.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_EJYUMy": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "How many gloves should your child have?",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">This is a big one.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Most kids train 1–3 times per week, plus matches at the weekend. That’s a lot of wear.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">If they’re using one pair for everything, the latex will wear out much quicker — especially on artificial pitches.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">We recommend:</p>\n <ul class=\"section-content__list\">\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">1 pair for training</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">1 pair saved for match day</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Even if they’re the same model, keeping a match pair fresh makes a huge difference in grip — and confidence.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/ba4d70ea203c43b3847bcc51cfd8b15afe07ceec_67a54fc9-b052-4399-95d3-fda87b345887.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_dTRCJP": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Why not all kids gloves are equal",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">Most brands either:</p>\n<ul class=\"section-content__list\">\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Cut corners on junior gloves (cheap materials, poor fit), or</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Use adult latex that isn't built for how kids play</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">We don’t.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Every junior model we make is built from the ground up:</p>\n<ul class=\"section-content__list\">\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Giga Latex for grip + long-term durability</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Reinforced palms to survive turf and repeated dives</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Junior-specific fit — not just adult gloves shrunk down</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Proper support — no gimmicks or hollow padding</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">If your child takes goalkeeping seriously — or is showing signs that they might — they need gloves that support their progress, not slow them down.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/370e0250aac54d9d1443ba5bd6185583a37e161d.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        }
      },
